.TH SAPL-LANGUAGE-SERVER 1 "2026-03-16" "SAPL 4.0.0" "SAPL Language Server"
.SH NAME
sapl-language-server \- language server for SAPL policy and test files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sapl-language-server
.RB [ \-\-socket
.RB [ \-\-port=\fIPORT\fR ]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sapl-language-server
implements the Language Server Protocol (LSP) for
.I .sapl
policy files and
.I .sapltest
test files.
.PP
Features include syntax error diagnostics, semantic validation,
context-aware content assist, document formatting, document symbols,
folding ranges, selection ranges, hover documentation, variable rename,
and semantic token highlighting.
.PP
By default the server communicates over standard input and output (stdio mode).
Editors launch the binary directly and connect via pipes.
.PP
In socket mode the server listens on a TCP port and accepts multiple
concurrent editor connections.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-socket
Listen on a TCP socket instead of stdio. The server binds to
.B localhost
only.
.TP
.BI \-\-port= PORT
TCP port for socket mode. Default:
.BR 5007 .
Ignored when running in stdio mode.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Normal shutdown.
.TP
.B 1
Startup error (e.g., port already in use).
.SH EXAMPLES
Start in stdio mode (typical editor integration):
.PP
.RS
.nf
sapl-language-server
.fi
.RE
.PP
Start in socket mode on the default port:
.PP
.RS
.nf
sapl-language-server --socket
.fi
.RE
.PP
Start in socket mode on a custom port:
.PP
.RS
.nf
sapl-language-server --socket --port=9090
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sapl (1)
.PP
Full documentation: <https://sapl.io>
